    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="236"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d236">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860C.48/564½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Polish Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kwapiszewski</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="57" xml:id="d236fn57">This note was handed to the Adviser on Political
                        Affairs, James C. Dunn, by the Polish Chargé with the remark that this
                        matter had been the subject of communications between the Polish Government
                        and the American Chargé in London, and not through the Polish Embassy in
                        Washington.</note>
                </head>
                <p>The Chargé d’Affaires ad interim of Poland presents his compliments to the
                    Secretary of State and, acting upon instructions of the Minister of Foreign
                    Affairs, begs to advise that Dr. Ludwik Rajchman was relieved of the duties of
                    delegate in the United States of the Polish Government for matters of relief for
                    civilian population of Poland.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-07">January 7,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                    <lb/> No. 738/SZ–14. </closer>
            </div>
